The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | CM reaches out to nun
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     CM reaches out to nun
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          The nun in Delhi on Friday                                  
	Bhubaneswar, Oct. 25: A day after the nun, who was allegedly raped in Kandhamal two months ago, expressed her lack of faith in Orissa police and demanded a CBI probe, the state government said it was prepared to conduct the identification parade of the accused at any place she chose.        
	The nun is requested to co-operate in the investigation and identification of the culprits, chief minister Naveen Patnaik said today. The government is prepared to conduct the test identification parade of the nine accused at any place in or outside the state, as chosen by the victim, he added.        
	The government also asked director-general of police and inspector-general (crime branch) to expedite the investigation into the case and identification of the accused, he said. Naveen said his government had decided to set up a fast-track court in Kandhamal for speedy disposal of riot-related cases, according to the direction of the Supreme Court. A special prosecutor would be appointed to look after the prosecution in the fast-track court, sources said.        
	Home secretary T.K. Mishra said the district collectors had been asked to complete the assessment of damage caused to the religious institutions including churches during the communal violence, within a fortnight.         
	We will consider to provide reasonable assistance for the repair or reconstruction of the damaged institutions on the basis of assessment reports, he said.        
	The Supreme Court had directed the government on Tuesday to consider providing reasonable assistance for the reconstruction of churches damaged during the recent communal violence.        
	Kandhamal collector has been advised to involve NGOs with good track record in the relief and rehabilitation work, said an official, adding that the district administration had been asked to see that adequate security was provided to the riot victims taking shelter at relief camps.        
	A formal request has also been made to the Centre for deployment of 53 companies of central paramilitary forces in Kandhamal till end of December, said the official.                                                                                                                                                                         
